## Fixes Found (1 minor + 1 judgment call)

### Minor (Tightening)

1. **Interview → ¥200M section** is the one seam rated below strong. The interview ends on his fear of "a life small enough to be fully understood" / a dream everyone can imagine; the next section opens cold on "By mid-2024 China's model war had become a marketing war." The strongest available bridge is already in the piece's own vocabulary — the ad blitz was precisely the *imaginable* strategy. Proposed one-clause edit to the topic sentence:

   > Current: "…and Moonshot fought it with money."
