   Carries the keyword across the seam and sharpens the later "The playbook was never his" payoff. No new argument added.

### Remaining Concern (your call, not a cohesion edit)

2. **Salakhutdinov's "What a huge win for the open-source community!" quote** (Fortune, July 2026) buttons the comeback section but is almost certainly a K3 reaction — and K3 isn't revealed until the next section. It reads fine as a general open-source-strategy reaction since the quote doesn't name K3, but if an editor pass touches that section, it's the one sequencing wobble left.

